The paper proposes a hybrid architecture for computing robust visual explanations using video data, which involves both hypothesis formation and belief revision. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves object tracking and motion analysis, which are relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper also involves reasoning about moving objects, which is relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
